20environment.%20One%20benefit%20to%20blockchain%20is%20security%20because%20the%20stored%20data%20cannot%20be%20edited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmed%20exploited%20a%20vulnerability%20in%20the%20exchange's%20smart%20contracts%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20US%20Attorney%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20submit%20falsified%20data%20that%20resulted%20in%20the%20contracts%20generating%20millions%20of%20dollars%20worth%20of%20inflated%20fees%20he%20hadn't%20earned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20smart%20contracts%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESmart%20contracts%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-blockchain-how-does-it-work-explainer-2017-11%23blockchains-could-eventually-replace-institutions-like-banks-and-law-firms-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblockchain%3C%2Fa%3E%20programs%20that%2C%20like%20a%20vending%20machine%2C%20execute%20specified%20functions%20when%20predetermined%20conditions%20are%20met.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20landlord%20leasing%20an%20apartment%20could%20use%20a%20smart%20contract%20in%20which%20the%20renter%20must%20transfer%20a%20security%20deposit%20to%20receive%20the%20apartment%20door%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmed%20was%20able%20to%20reverse%20engineer%20the%20steps%20needed%20to%20make%20the%20exchanges%20pay%20out%20massive%20sums%20by%20using%20specialized%20skills%20he%20developed%20working%20for%20Amazon%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Attorney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmed%20then%20attempted%20to%20cover%20his%20tracks%20by%20negotiating%20with%20the%20unnamed%20crypto%20exchange.%20He%20said%20he'd%20agree%20to%20return%20all%20of%20the%20stolen%20funds%2C%20less%20%241.5%20million%20if%20the%20exchange%20agreed%20not%20to%20contact%20law%20enforcement%20about%20the%20hack%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eprosecutors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20hacking%20the%20first%20exchange%2C%20Ahmed%20targeted%20Nirvana's%20cryptocurrency%2C%20ANA%2C%20exploiting%20a%20function%20of%20the%20cryptocurrency%20intended%20to%20inflate%20each%20token's%20price%20after%20a%20large%20sum%20was%20purchased.%20Using%20a%20workaround%20in%20Nirvana's%20smart%20contract%2C%20Ahmed%20could%20buy%20%2410%20million%20worth%20of%20ANA%20tokens%20at%20an%20artificially%20lowered%20price%20and%20sell%20them%20for%20%243.6%20million%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eprofit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNirvana%20offered%20AHMED%20a%20'bug%20bounty'%20of%20as%20much%20as%20%24600%2C000%20to%20return%20the%20stolen%20funds%2C%20but%20AHMED%20instead%20demanded%20%241.4%20million%2C%20did%20not%20reach%20agreement%20with%20Nirvana%2C%20and%20kept%20all%20the%20stolen%20funds%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Attorney%20statement.%C2%A0%26quot%3BThe%20%243.6%20million%20AHMED%20stole%20represented%20approximately%20all%20the%20funds%20possessed%20by%20Nirvana%2C%20which%20as%20a%20result%20shut%20down%20shortly%20after%20AHMED's%20attack.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmed%C2%A0stole%20over%20%2412%20million%20and%20%26quot%3Btried%20to%20cover%20his%20tracks%20by%C2%A0swapping%C2%A0stolen%20crypto%20for%20Monero%2C%C2%A0using%20cryptocurrency%20mixers%2C%C2%A0hopping%C2%A0across%20blockchains%2C%C2%A0and%C2%A0utilizing%C2%A0overseas%20crypto%20exchanges%2C%26quot%3B%20US%20Attorney%20Damian%20Williams%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20United%20States%20Attorney%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20New%20York%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20theory%2C%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20smart%20contract%20is%20to%20eliminate%20the%20risk%20of%20fraud%20by%20a%20middleman%20or%2C%20say%2C%20a%20broker.%20However%2C%20the%20program%20has%20been%20vulnerable%20to%20attacks%20by%20hackers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20%242.2%20billion%20in%20cryptocurrency%20was%20stolen%20in%202022%20from%20Decentralized%20Finance%20(DeFi)%20projects%2C%20allowing%20people%20to%20carry%20out%20financial%20transactions%20without%20needing%20third%20parties%20or%20financial%20institutions%20such%20as%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F09%2F28%2Ftechnology%2Fcrypto-hacks-defi.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20many%20of%20the%20thefts%20were%20carried%20out%20by%20taking%20advantage%20of%20vulnerabilities%20in%20smart%20contracts.%20Since%20smart%20contracts%20are%20built%20upon%20open-source%20code%2C%20hackers%20can%20make%20themselves%20aware%20of%20the%20inner%20workings%20of%20the%20software%20and%20take%20advantage%20of%20any%20vulnerabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-engineer-hacking-cryptocurrency-nirvana-solana-what-are-smart-contracts-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702788796000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657e49e550edbc52a8651115%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-engineer-hacking-cryptocurrency-nirvana-solana-what-are-smart-contracts-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20former%20Amazon%20engineer%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20hacking%20two%20crypto%20exchanges%20and%20stealing%20%2412.3%20million%20in%20the%20first%20ever%20conviction%20involving%20smart%20contracts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktangalakislippert%40businessinsider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert%2CLloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A69%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-engineer-hacking-cryptocurrency-nirvana-solana-what-are-smart-contracts-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kim%20Sae%20Ron%20returns%20to%20Instagram!%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702788732000%2C