mps-rs-2-26-trn-tcs-infosys-biggest-gaines-123121700143_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Men's%20Eggs%2C%20Women's%20Sperm%3A%20Stem%20Cell%20Science%20May%20Change%20How%20We%20Reproduce%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20soon%20be%20possible%20to%20coax%20human%20skin%20cells%20into%20becoming%20functional%20eggs%20and%20sperm%20using%20a%20technique%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9Cin%20vitro%20gametogenesis%E2%80%9D.%20This%20involves%20the%20creation%20(genesis)%20of%20eggs%20and%20sperm%20(gametes)%20outside%20the%20human%20body%20(in%20vitro).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20theory%2C%20a%20skin%20cell%20from%20a%20man%20could%20be%20turned%20into%20an%20egg%20and%20a%20skin%20cell%20from%20a%20woman%20can%20become%20a%20sperm.%20Then%20there's%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20child%20having%20multiple%20genetically-related%20parents%2C%20or%20only%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20scientists%20believe%20human%20applications%20of%20in%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20are%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statnews.com%2F2023%2F10%2F02%2Fivg-ivf-replacement-reproductive-technology-hype%2F%5C%22%3Elong%20way%20off%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20scientists%20who%20work%20on%20human%20stem%20cells%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10579208%2F%5C%22%3Eactively%20working%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20overcoming%20the%20barriers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statnews.com%2F2023%2F04%2F08%2Fivf-eggs-hormones-gameto-reproductive-fertilo%2F%5C%22%3ENew%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2F2021%2F10%2F28%2F1038172%2Fconception-eggs-reproduction-vitro-gametogenesis%2F%5C%22%3Ebiotechnology%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2023%2F04%2F24%2Fthe-future-of-fertility%5C%22%3Estart-ups%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20also%20seeking%20to%20commercialise%20this%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20we%20know%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20human%20in%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20and%20why%20we%20need%20to%20start%20talking%20about%20this%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EIs%20the%20technology%20available%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20begins%20with%20%E2%80%9Cpluripotent%20stem%20cells%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20cell%20that%20can%20develop%20into%20many%20different%20cell%20types.%20The%20aim%20is%20to%20persuade%20these%20stem%20cells%20to%20become%20eggs%20or%20sperm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20techniques%20could%20use%20stem%20cells%20taken%20from%20early%20embryos.%20But%20scientists%20have%20also%20worked%20out%20how%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurostemcell.org%2Fstemcellshorts-what-are-induced-pluripotent-stem-cells%5C%22%3Erevert%20adult%20cells%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20pluripotent%20state.%20This%20opens%20up%20the%20possibility%20of%20creating%20eggs%20or%20sperm%20that%20%E2%80%9Cbelong%20to%E2%80%9D%20an%20existing%20human%20adult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnimal%20studies%20have%20been%20promising.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2F490146b%5C%22%3E2012%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20scientists%20created%20live-born%20baby%20mice%20using%20eggs%20that%20began%20their%20life%20as%20skin%20cells%20on%20a%20mouse%20tail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20the%20technique%20has%20been%20used%20to%20facilitate%20same-sex%20reproduction.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20scientists%20created%20mouse%20pups%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fd41586-023-00717-7%5C%22%3Etwo%20genetic%20fathers%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20transforming%20skin%20cells%20from%20male%20mice%20into%20eggs.%20Mouse%20pups%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fd41586-018-06999-6%5C%22%3Etwo%20genetic%20mothers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20been%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22440%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F1ocWjHJgKcc%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22260%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cspan%3EHow%20scientists%20bred%20mice%20with%20two%20fathers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20not%20yet%20managed%20to%20adapt%20these%20techniques%20to%20create%20human%20gametes.%20Perhaps%20because%20the%20technology%20is%20still%20in%20its%20infancy%2C%20Australia's%20legal%20and%20regulatory%20systems%20do%20not%20address%20whether%20and%20how%20the%20technology%20should%20be%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20National%20Health%20and%20Medical%20Research%20Council's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhmrc.gov.au%2Fabout-us%2Fpublications%2Fart%5C%22%3Eassisted%20reproduction%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20were%20updated%20in%202023%2C%20do%20not%20include%20specific%20guidance%20for%20in%20vitro-derived%20gametes.%20These%20guidelines%20will%20need%20to%20be%20updated%20if%20in%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20becomes%20viable%20in%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20potential%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20distinct%20clinical%20applications%20of%20this%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20in%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20could%20streamline%20IVF.%20Egg%20retrieval%20currently%20involves%20repeated%20hormone%20injections%2C%20a%20minor%20surgical%20procedure%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinic.org%2Fdiseases-conditions%2Fovarian-hyperstimulation-syndrome-ohss%2Fsymptoms-causes%2Fsyc-20354697%5C%22%3Erisk%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20overstimulating%20the%20ovaries.%20In%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20could%20eliminate%20these%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20technology%20could%20circumvent%20some%20forms%20of%20medical%20infertility.%20For%20example%2C%20it%20could%20be%20used%20to%20generate%20eggs%20for%20women%20born%20without%20functioning%20ovaries%20or%20following%20early%20menopause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20the%20technology%20could%20allow%20same-sex%20couples%20to%20have%20children%20who%20are%20genetically%20related%20to%20both%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ELegal%2C%20regulatory%20and%20ethical%20issues%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20technology%20becomes%20viable%2C%20in%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20will%20alter%20the%20dynamics%20of%20how%20we%20create%20families%20in%20unprecedented%20ways.%20How%20we%20should%20respond%20requires%20careful%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Is%20it%20safe%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECareful%20trials%2C%20rigorous%20monitoring%2C%20and%20follow-up%20of%20any%20children%20born%20will%20be%20essential%20%E2%80%93%20as%20it%20has%20been%20for%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fmaeves-law-would-let-ivf-parents-access-technology-to-prevent-mitochondrial-disease-heres-what-the-senate-is-debating-176668%5C%22%3Ereproductive%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Frest-assured-ivf-babies-grow-into-healthy-adults-23432%5C%22%3Etechnologies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20IVF.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Is%20it%20equitable%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20issues%20relate%20to%20access.%20It%20might%20seem%20unjust%20if%20the%20technology%20is%20only%20available%20to%20the%20wealthy.%20Public%20funding%20could%20help%20%E2%80%93%20but%20whether%20this%20is%20appropriate%20depends%20on%20whether%20the%20state%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fideas-for-australia-rethinking-funding-and-priorities-in-ivf-should-the-state-pay-for-people-to-have-babies-57036%5C%22%3Eought%20to%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20people's%20reproductive%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Should%20we%20restrict%20access%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20pregnancy%20is%20rare%20in%20older%20women%2C%20largely%20because%20egg%20count%20and%20quality%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.betterhealth.vic.gov.au%2Fhealth%2Fconditionsandtreatments%2Fage-and-fertility%5C%22%3Edecline%20with%20age%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20would%20theoretically%20provide%20%E2%80%9Cfresh%E2%80%9D%20eggs%20for%20women%20of%20any%20age.%20But%20helping%20older%20women%20become%20parents%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC5566409%2F%5C%22%3Econtroversial%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20due%20to%20physical%2C%20psychological%20and%20other%20factors%20associated%20with%20having%20babies%20later%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20We'd%20still%20need%20surrogates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20took%20skin%20cells%20from%20each%20male%20partner%20and%20created%20an%20embryo%2C%20that%20embryo%20would%20still%20need%20a%20surrogate%20to%20carry%20the%20pregnancy.%20Unfortunately%2C%20Australia%20has%20a%20shortfall%20of%20surrogates.%20International%20surrogacy%20provides%20an%20alternative%2C%20but%20carries%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fits-hard-to-find-a-surrogate-in-australia-but-heading-overseas-comes-with-risks-206182%5C%22%3Elegal%2C%20ethical%20and%20practical%20difficulties%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Unless%20access%20to%20surrogacy%20is%20improved%20domestically%2C%20benefits%20to%20male%20couples%20will%20be%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Who%20are%20the%20legal%20parents%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20also%20raises%20questions%20about%20who%20are%20the%20future%20child's%20legal%20parents.%20We%20already%20see%20related%20legal%20debates%20surrounding%20non-traditional%20families%20formed%20through%20surrogacy%2C%20egg%20donation%20and%20sperm%20donation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20could%20theoretically%20also%20be%20used%20to%20create%20children%20with%20more%20than%20two%20genetic%20parents%2C%20or%20with%20only%20one.%20These%20possibilities%20likewise%20require%20us%20to%20update%20our%20current%20understandings%20of%20parenthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20far%20is%20too%20far%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20potential%20uses%20already%20mentioned%2C%20same-sex%20reproduction%20is%20the%20most%20controversial.%20The%20reproductive%20limitations%20imposed%20by%20being%20in%20a%20same-sex%20relationship%20are%20sometimes%20seen%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csocial%E2%80%9D%20form%20of%20infertility%20the%20medical%20profession%20is%20not%20obligated%20to%20fix.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20moral%20stakes%2C%20however%2C%20are%20virtually%20identical%20regardless%20of%20whether%20in%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20is%20used%20by%20same-sex%20or%20opposite-sex%20couples.%20Both%20uses%20of%20the%20technology%20fulfil%20exactly%20the%20same%20goal%3A%20helping%20couples%20fulfil%20their%20desire%20to%20have%20a%20child%20genetically%20related%20to%20both%20parents.%20It%20would%20be%20unjust%20to%20deny%20access%20to%20only%20one%20of%20these%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20same-sex%20reproduction%20is%20only%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20iceberg.%20In%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20could%20theoretically%20facilitate%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6973109%2F%5C%22%3Esolo%20reproduction%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20by%20deriving%20both%20eggs%20and%20sperm%20from%20the%20same%20individual.%20Interestingly%2C%20a%20child%20created%20this%20way%20would%20not%20be%20a%20clone%20of%20its%20parent%2C%20since%20the%20process%20of%20gamete%20formation%20would%20shuffle%20the%20parent's%20genetic%20material%20and%20create%20a%20genetically%20distinct%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOr%20people%20could%20engage%20in%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4215291%2F%5C%22%3Emultiplex%20parenting%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20combining%20genetic%20material%20from%20more%20than%20two%20individuals.%20Imagine%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20two%20couples%20create%20embryos%20via%20IVF.%20In%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20could%20then%20be%20used%20to%20derive%20eggs%20and%20sperm%20from%20each%20of%20these%20two%20separate%20embryos%2C%20which%20could%20subsequently%20be%20used%20to%20conceive%20a%20single%20child%20that%20is%20genetically%20related%20to%20all%20four%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%20vitro%20gametogenesis%20could%20revolutionise%20prenatal%20genetic%20selection.%20We'd%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frmanetwork.com%2Fblog%2Fnumber-of-eggs-good-ivf-in-vitro-fertilization%2F%5C%22%3Emany%20more%20embryos%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20available%20during%20regular%20IVF%20to%20screen%20for%20genetic%20diseases%20and%20traits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20it%20would%20be%20urgent%20to%20discuss%20%E2%80%9Cdesigner%20babies%E2%80%9D%2C%20eugenics%2C%20and%20whether%20we%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbioedge.org%2Fbioethics-d75%2Fsavulescu-interviewed-on-procreative-beneficence%2F%5C%22%3Emoral%20obligation%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20conceive%20children%20with%20the%20best%20chance%20of%20a%20good%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWe%20need%20to%20start%20talking%20about%20this%20now%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20law%20and%20ethics%20can%20lag%20behind%20new%20technologies%2C%20particularly%20when%20their%20implications%20are%20as%20profound%20and%20far-reaching%20as%20the%20implications%20of%20in%20vitro%20gametogenesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20discuss%20how%20this%20technology%20should%20be%20regulated%20before%20it%20is%20rolled%20out.%20Given%20how%20rapidly%20the%20science%20is%20developing%2C%20we%20should%20begin%20this%20discussion%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELaura%20Smith%2C%20a%20masters%20student%20from%20Monash%20University%2C%20contributed%20to%20this%20article.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F219005%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C