estigation-elevated-lead-levels-cinnamon-applesauce-pouches-november-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etainted%20on%20purpose%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Food%20and%20Drug%20Administration%20said%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fsafety%2Frecalls-market-withdrawals-safety-alerts%2Fwanabana-recalls-wanabana-weis-and-schnucks-apple-cinnamon-fruit-puree-pouches-cinnamon-apple-sauce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWanaBana%20recalled%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20WanaBana%2C%20Weis%2C%20and%20Schnucks%20apple%20cinnamon%20fruit%20pur%C3%A9e%20pouches%20and%20cinnamon%20apple%20sauce%20in%20November%20due%20to%20reportedly%20elevated%20lead%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA's%20deputy%20commissioner%20for%20human%20foods%2C%20Jim%20Jones%2C%20said%20that%20signs%20point%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F12%2F14%2Fapplesauce-pouches-may-have-been-contaminated-on-purpose-fda-foods-chief-says-00131797%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintentional%20act%20on%20the%20part%20of%20someone%20in%20the%20supply%20chain%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Politico%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20added%20that%20an%20ongoing%20investigation%20seeks%20to%20uncover%20who%20may%20have%20tainted%20the%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pouches%20may%20have%20been%20subjected%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Ffood%2Fcompliance-enforcement-food%2Feconomically-motivated-adulteration-food-fraud%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Beconomically%20motivated%20adulteration%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfood%20fraud%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20FDA%20said.%20This%20happens%20when%20a%20valuable%20ingredient%20is%20intentionally%20left%20out%2C%20taken%20out%2C%20or%20substituted%20without%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20said%20one%20example%20of%20this%20is%20when%20lead-based%20dyes%20are%20introduced%20to%20alter%20the%20color%20of%20a%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELead%20is%20toxic%20to%20humans%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Flead%2Fprevention%2Fhealth-effects.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren%20should%20be%20protected%20from%20exposure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention.%20Lead%20poisoning%20is%20not%20always%20apparent%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atsdr.cdc.gov%2Fcsem%2Fleadtoxicity%2Fsigns_and_symptoms.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20short-term%20exposure%20can%20include%20headaches%2C%20abdominal%20pain%2C%20vomiting%2C%20and%20anemia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20this%20is%20an%20ongoing%20investigation%2C%20the%20FDA%20can%20only%20confirm%20this%20is%20one%20of%20the%20theories%20at%20this%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20FDA%20spokesperson%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%2C%20per%20NBC%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20is%20inspecting%20a%20facility%20in%20Ecuador%20that%20produces%20the%20pouches%2C%20it%20said.%20Ecuadorian%20authorities%20independently%20found%20traces%20of%20lead%20in%20the%20cinnamon%20that%20surpassed%20the%20country's%20limit%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FDA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20reported%20on%20December%208%20that%20there%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Flead%2Fnews%2Flead-poisoning-outbreak-linked-to-cinnamon-applesauce-pouches.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E125%20reported%20cases%20of%20lead%20poisoning%20linked%20to%20the%20recalled%20products%3C%2Fa%3E.%2046%20have%20been%20confirmed%2C%2068%20are%20probable%2C%20and%2011%20are%20suspected%2C%20it%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20cases%20were%20documented%20across%2022%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA%20said%20consumers%20should%20discard%20the%20recalled%20pouches%20if%20they%20still%20have%20any%20in%20their%20homes.%20The%20products%20have%20a%20long%20shelf%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F